1
00:00:02,069 --> 00:00:03,867
- <i>Previously:</i> - Can I help you?

2
00:00:03,937 --> 00:00:06,202
My name's Miles
Browne. I'm your father.

3
00:00:06,273 --> 00:00:08,469
Go home. I think
you're having a stroke.

4
00:00:09,176 --> 00:00:10,542
I have terminal cancer.

5
00:00:10,611 --> 00:00:13,080
I waited for you and you left.

6
00:00:13,146 --> 00:00:15,581
I thought about you every day.

7
00:00:18,719 --> 00:00:21,712
It's good we're not roommates
anymore 'cause I couldn't do this.

8
00:00:22,689 --> 00:00:26,023
Having sex doesn't make us a
thing. You need to see other women.

9
00:00:26,093 --> 00:00:27,893
- Why? I don't really want to...
- No excuses.

10
00:00:27,928 --> 00:00:30,022
Do you want to come
back to my place for more?

11
00:00:30,097 --> 00:00:33,761
Just sleeping with you isn't good for
me. I want to give Heather a chance.

12
00:00:37,004 --> 00:00:38,939
- Thanks for cooking.
- Mm-hm.

13
00:00:39,006 --> 00:00:41,840
And the new skillet. The
chicken was delicious.

14
00:00:41,909 --> 00:00:44,777
What'd I tell you?
Cast iron kicks ass.

15
00:00:45,312 --> 00:00:48,305
Wait till you sear a steak in it.
You won't believe the difference.

16
00:00:48,382 --> 00:00:49,543
I'll definitely try it.

17
00:00:51,919 --> 00:00:53,182
So you up for a movie?

18
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:57,248
Actually, I thought
maybe we could just... talk.

19
00:00:58,725 --> 00:01:00,591
Well, we spent
all night talking.

20
00:01:01,094 --> 00:01:04,587
Yeah, about our jobs,
the news, the weather.

21
00:01:05,299 --> 00:01:06,299
But...

22
00:01:07,467 --> 00:01:08,467
we, uh...

23
00:01:09,202 --> 00:01:11,034
never really talked
about the past.

24
00:01:12,072 --> 00:01:14,837
We did. When you
were at the hospital.

25
00:01:15,642 --> 00:01:16,642
Barely.

26
00:01:19,112 --> 00:01:20,375
Have you forgiven me?

27
00:01:28,922 --> 00:01:29,922
You know, I...

28
00:01:30,891 --> 00:01:32,291
I'd rather just watch a movie.

29
00:01:32,359 --> 00:01:34,385
- Claire, I don't...
- If you want to join, great.

30
00:01:34,461 --> 00:01:36,930
If not, let's just
call it a night.

31
00:01:39,266 --> 00:01:41,326
Okay. Movie it is.

32
00:01:42,302 --> 00:01:43,361
Okay.

33
00:01:50,010 --> 00:01:53,105
- How'd your presentation go?
- It was...

34
00:01:53,947 --> 00:01:54,947
long.

35
00:01:55,983 --> 00:01:57,975
Didn't you do laundry yesterday?

36
00:01:58,051 --> 00:02:01,180
I'm not doing laundry. I'm
packing. For our camping trip.

37
00:02:01,989 --> 00:02:03,958
We've done nothing
but work for three weeks.

38
00:02:04,024 --> 00:02:06,994
And neither of
us feels... better.

39
00:02:07,060 --> 00:02:10,997
A weekend in the woods
isn't going to change anything.

40
00:02:11,064 --> 00:02:13,056
Not to mention you can't
even sleep on a couch,

41
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:14,897
much less outside on the ground.

42
00:02:14,968 --> 00:02:16,630
I agree,

43
00:02:16,703 --> 00:02:19,673
it's going to be a challenge,
but that's the point.

44
00:02:20,707 --> 00:02:23,108
The further outside our
comfort zones we go,

45
00:02:23,176 --> 00:02:24,474
the more distracted we'll be.

46
00:02:54,241 --> 00:02:57,302
Whoa, man! It's me,
okay? Don't shoot!

47
00:02:57,377 --> 00:02:58,436
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine!

48
00:02:58,512 --> 00:03:00,174
Can you put the
gun down, please?

49
00:03:01,348 --> 00:03:03,749
I opened the door and the
alarm went off, it's broken.

50
00:03:03,817 --> 00:03:05,285
Oh, thank God.

51
00:03:05,886 --> 00:03:07,650
- Man.
- I thought somebody, uh...

52
00:03:09,022 --> 00:03:10,022
Hi.

53
00:03:11,058 --> 00:03:12,058
Hi.

54
00:03:17,864 --> 00:03:18,864
It's not loaded.

55
00:03:20,834 --> 00:03:21,858
Yeah, good.

56
00:03:21,935 --> 00:03:24,200
No, no, not good. I...

57
00:03:24,271 --> 00:03:27,139
store this loaded. Always.

58
00:03:27,207 --> 00:03:28,300
I unloaded it.

59
00:03:29,509 --> 00:03:32,240
For this exact reason.
You could've killed me.

60
00:03:32,312 --> 00:03:35,373
And if you had been an
intruder, you could've killed me.

61
00:03:35,449 --> 00:03:37,782
I'm not an intruder.
I'm me. Hello!

62
00:03:38,752 --> 00:03:40,721
You had the gun
pointed right at my head!

63
00:03:40,787 --> 00:03:44,986
No, I was aiming center mass.
My finger wasn't even on the trigger.

64
00:03:45,058 --> 00:03:47,323
Thank you very much for
the apology, appreciate it.

65
00:03:47,394 --> 00:03:48,394
Apology?

66
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:52,525
What in the world would make
you think that it was okay...

67
00:03:53,166 --> 00:03:54,759
to unload my gun?

68
00:03:54,835 --> 00:03:59,967
You almost shot me center mass,
okay? But by all means, don't apologize!

69
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:02,100
I did not almost shoot you!

70
00:04:02,175 --> 00:04:04,235
And if you don't stop
with the apology...

71
00:04:05,412 --> 00:04:06,675
I'm going to bed.

72
00:04:07,681 --> 00:04:08,681
Alone.

73
00:04:23,697 --> 00:04:26,257
The discoloration is a
deeper red than her last exam.

74
00:04:27,601 --> 00:04:30,298
- And it's warm to the touch.
- Ow.

75
00:04:30,370 --> 00:04:32,601
Sorry. How long
has it been tender?

76
00:04:32,672 --> 00:04:35,403
Uh... About a week.

77
00:04:35,475 --> 00:04:37,637
Well, it's not a bruise
or muscle strain.

78
00:04:37,711 --> 00:04:39,646
The AV malformation's growing,

79
00:04:40,147 --> 00:04:43,311
which is why I've been
recommending surgery since she was 5.

80
00:04:43,383 --> 00:04:47,150
- And I've agreed every time.
- It's the first time there's been pain.

81
00:04:47,220 --> 00:04:50,122
And the meds and the nutritional
supplements have been working.

82
00:04:50,190 --> 00:04:51,214
No, they haven't.

83
00:04:51,291 --> 00:04:53,817
And puberty will accelerate
the growth even more,

84
00:04:53,894 --> 00:04:56,329
which puts her at a high risk
for spontaneous hemorrhage.

85
00:04:56,897 --> 00:04:59,526
Turtleneck sweaters are
definitely not the solution any longer.

86
00:04:59,599 --> 00:05:00,897
She needs the surgery.

87
00:05:05,105 --> 00:05:06,300
When?

88
00:05:06,373 --> 00:05:08,035
We can admit her
and start the prep now.

89
00:05:09,976 --> 00:05:10,976
Awesome.

90
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:15,142
I hate turtlenecks.

91
00:05:17,484 --> 00:05:21,319
Your EKG's normal, cholesterol's low,
and I didn't see any concerning moles.

92
00:05:21,388 --> 00:05:22,754
I wear SPF 50 every day.

93
00:05:23,857 --> 00:05:25,257
There was one thing.

94
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:27,851
I noticed that you previously
had been on antidepressants.

95
00:05:27,928 --> 00:05:29,658
I stopped taking
those nine months ago.

96
00:05:29,729 --> 00:05:32,608
They didn't help, and I found an
alternative therapy that's working great.

97
00:05:32,632 --> 00:05:34,658
Wonderful. Cognitive
behavioral therapy?

98
00:05:34,734 --> 00:05:35,565
No.

99
00:05:35,635 --> 00:05:37,661
Uh, I'm injecting
a psilocybin serum

100
00:05:37,737 --> 00:05:40,400
that I make from hallucinogenic
mushrooms I grow in my basement.

101
00:05:43,176 --> 00:05:46,874
Okay, that's... crazy. You
need to stop that immediately.

102
00:05:46,947 --> 00:05:49,815
There's tons of studies
online that show that psilocybin

103
00:05:49,883 --> 00:05:52,114
causes dopamine surges
that treat depression.

104
00:05:52,185 --> 00:05:54,120
And even more studies
that show that people

105
00:05:54,187 --> 00:05:55,985
who self-medicate
with street drugs

106
00:05:56,056 --> 00:05:58,457
end up more depressed,
addicted and sometimes even dead.

107
00:05:58,525 --> 00:06:01,120
I spent a year researching
mushroom cultivation

108
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:03,322
and learning how to
extract the psilocybin.

109
00:06:03,396 --> 00:06:06,491
And most importantly, this is the
first treatment that's ever worked.

110
00:06:07,934 --> 00:06:09,095
I've never felt better.

111
00:06:12,305 --> 00:06:13,905
At least let me do
some additional tests

112
00:06:13,940 --> 00:06:15,780
to make sure there
aren't adverse side effects.

113
00:06:15,809 --> 00:06:18,711
Sure. I'm always open
to new information.

114
00:06:25,819 --> 00:06:28,084
Good morning.
How can I help you?

115
00:06:28,154 --> 00:06:30,123
We're here to camp
at Yosemite Creek.

116
00:06:30,190 --> 00:06:32,386
Great. You have a reservation?

117
00:06:32,459 --> 00:06:35,258
- Reservation?
- Campsites are reservation only.

118
00:06:35,962 --> 00:06:37,555
That's not true.

119
00:06:37,631 --> 00:06:40,100
There are 27 first-come,
first-serve campsites.

120
00:06:40,166 --> 00:06:43,830
There were 27
campsites at 6 a.m.

121
00:06:43,904 --> 00:06:46,897
By 6:45, they were all taken.

122
00:06:47,574 --> 00:06:50,874
- Need you to turn the car around.
- No, we need to go camping.

123
00:06:50,944 --> 00:06:52,003
Sir...

124
00:06:52,078 --> 00:06:55,173
- I understand you're upset, but...
- No, you don't understand

125
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:56,876
- at all why...
- Shaun, it's okay.

126
00:06:56,950 --> 00:06:59,112
We'll find another place
to camp. Thank you.

127
00:07:07,427 --> 00:07:10,522
Tighten up. Now work
from the outside in.

128
00:07:10,597 --> 00:07:12,725
Eliminate any arterial feeders.

129
00:07:14,801 --> 00:07:17,669
This would be a lot easier if they'd
let me do this seven years ago.

130
00:07:17,737 --> 00:07:19,933
It's not their fault.
They're scared of surgery

131
00:07:20,006 --> 00:07:21,474
for their 12-year-old child.

132
00:07:22,309 --> 00:07:24,301
They're arrogant. And stubborn.

133
00:07:26,179 --> 00:07:27,179
You're quiet.

134
00:07:28,715 --> 00:07:30,115
Oh, sorry.

135
00:07:30,183 --> 00:07:32,675
Well, I was actually thinking
about my own parents.

136
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:36,115
Miles thinks that we
should "deal with the past,"

137
00:07:36,189 --> 00:07:38,158
so there's not a
barrier between us.

138
00:07:39,025 --> 00:07:42,928
Things have been going pretty good.
You know, why mess with success?

139
00:07:42,996 --> 00:07:46,558
I agree. When it comes to parents,
some things, in fact many things,

140
00:07:46,633 --> 00:07:48,101
should just be left unsaid.

141
00:07:48,168 --> 00:07:50,831
Says the guy who doesn't
have a relationship with his.

142
00:07:50,904 --> 00:07:54,204
Yeah. Because I said things
that should have been unsaid.

143
00:07:54,808 --> 00:07:56,140
Well, I agree with Miles.

144
00:07:56,209 --> 00:07:58,974
I mean, it's not gonna be
an easy conversation, but...

145
00:07:59,846 --> 00:08:01,576
wounds that aren't
treated get worse.

146
00:08:03,316 --> 00:08:05,461
There's blood in her ET tube.

147
00:08:05,485 --> 00:08:07,420
Must be a bleeder in the airway.

148
00:08:07,487 --> 00:08:10,013
Retract the wound.

149
00:08:14,661 --> 00:08:18,325
The research on psilocybin for
drug-resistant depression is promising.

150
00:08:18,865 --> 00:08:20,025
Apex of the lungs look clear.

151
00:08:20,066 --> 00:08:22,144
There's a difference between
"promising" and "proven."

152
00:08:22,168 --> 00:08:24,330
Not to mention a drug
made by professionals

153
00:08:24,404 --> 00:08:27,169
versus some guy growing
mushrooms in his basement.

154
00:08:27,941 --> 00:08:30,638
You're the most skeptical guy I
know about alternative medicine,

155
00:08:30,710 --> 00:08:32,770
- but this you agree with?
- I'm not surprised.

156
00:08:33,613 --> 00:08:36,549
- That Park's a total hypocrite?
- That you two disagree.

157
00:08:37,817 --> 00:08:40,184
You never agree on anything.

158
00:08:40,253 --> 00:08:41,721
I think you just...

159
00:08:42,789 --> 00:08:45,384
enjoy arguing with each other.

160
00:08:46,693 --> 00:08:47,693
You need to get closer.

161
00:08:50,864 --> 00:08:53,527
Can you focus on
the left inferior lobe?

162
00:08:55,802 --> 00:08:57,430
- What is that?
- A lesion.

163
00:08:57,504 --> 00:08:59,200
A fungal lesion.

164
00:09:11,084 --> 00:09:13,178
This isn't camping,
it's tailgating.

165
00:09:13,253 --> 00:09:17,054
There's trees, a place we
can pitch a tent and build a fire.

166
00:09:19,959 --> 00:09:21,951
It smells like gasoline.

167
00:09:23,363 --> 00:09:24,363
Oh.

168
00:09:25,131 --> 00:09:27,293
I think their generator
might have a leak.

169
00:09:28,134 --> 00:09:30,296
Just what you want
right next to a campfire.

170
00:09:35,341 --> 00:09:37,333
We have a view of the lake.

171
00:09:38,378 --> 00:09:39,641
It's pretty, isn't it?

172
00:09:41,281 --> 00:09:42,281
Yeah.

173
00:10:05,939 --> 00:10:08,431
We had to abort the laser
surgery due to a bleed,

174
00:10:08,508 --> 00:10:11,239
but she's conscious and
stable now in post-op recovery.

175
00:10:11,311 --> 00:10:13,803
The AVM infiltrated too
deep into the upper lobe

176
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:15,473
of the lung to
ablate with the laser.

177
00:10:15,548 --> 00:10:18,450
We'll have to go back in and remove
her collarbone for better access.

178
00:10:19,352 --> 00:10:22,584
Another surgery?
To remove her bone?

179
00:10:22,655 --> 00:10:25,386
We'll put it back after
we excise the AVM.

180
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:27,791
She'll have to wear a
brace until the bone heals.

181
00:10:27,861 --> 00:10:29,887
Vascular malformations
are chameleons.

182
00:10:29,963 --> 00:10:32,228
It's hard to tell where
abnormal blood vessels end

183
00:10:32,298 --> 00:10:33,596
and normal ones begin.

184
00:10:33,666 --> 00:10:37,228
Well, you were all a lot more confident
in your assessment this morning.

185
00:10:37,303 --> 00:10:39,465
- We want to take our daughter home.
- Yeah.

186
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:42,937
- Now.
- I'm sorry. That's not possible.

187
00:10:43,009 --> 00:10:45,103
The laser surgery caused
weakening in the AVM,

188
00:10:45,178 --> 00:10:47,238
which means it could
rebleed at any time.

189
00:10:55,255 --> 00:10:56,255
Okay.

190
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:01,660
Okay.

191
00:11:02,162 --> 00:11:04,597
You're lucky. If you'd
scheduled your physical later,

192
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:06,257
your liver and lungs
would be failing.

193
00:11:08,434 --> 00:11:09,766
And after the surgery?

194
00:11:10,970 --> 00:11:12,461
What about my depression?

195
00:11:12,539 --> 00:11:15,202
You're asking if you can continue
a treatment that's killing you?

196
00:11:17,577 --> 00:11:20,240
Before I started the
psilocybin injections...

197
00:11:21,281 --> 00:11:22,806
I was miserable.

198
00:11:22,882 --> 00:11:24,441
I couldn't sleep,

199
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:25,951
I barely ate.

200
00:11:27,220 --> 00:11:30,452
I can't bear to face
that darkness again.

201
00:11:34,527 --> 00:11:38,726
I don't know if it's the
psilocybin or placebo effect,

202
00:11:39,365 --> 00:11:42,062
or something else
neither of us understands.

203
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:45,235
But if you found
the light once...

204
00:11:47,273 --> 00:11:48,536
you can find it again.

205
00:12:06,326 --> 00:12:07,326
Okay.

206
00:12:07,827 --> 00:12:08,920
It's a nice fire.

207
00:12:11,097 --> 00:12:12,588
I used the teepee method.

208
00:12:31,184 --> 00:12:33,676
I'm thinking open thoracotomy
and midline laparotomy.

209
00:12:33,753 --> 00:12:36,086
We might be able to use
minimally invasive scope surgery

210
00:12:36,155 --> 00:12:37,155
to get the big lesions

211
00:12:37,190 --> 00:12:39,489
and attack the rest
post-operatively with anti-fungals.

212
00:12:39,559 --> 00:12:41,460
More like minimally effective.

213
00:12:41,527 --> 00:12:43,519
Better to be aggressive,
take them out at once.

214
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:45,861
That's a huge operation
with a long, painful recovery.

215
00:12:45,932 --> 00:12:47,298
He has a huge problem.

216
00:12:47,367 --> 00:12:50,201
This lesion looks like it
extends behind the liver.

217
00:12:53,706 --> 00:12:57,666
You're the senior surgical resident.
You need to start making these calls.

218
00:12:58,278 --> 00:12:59,769
I'm not so sure about that.

219
00:13:02,248 --> 00:13:05,741
I'm sorry, but I question
Dr. Park's objectivity

220
00:13:05,818 --> 00:13:08,117
when it comes to
Dr. Reznick's ideas.

221
00:13:08,187 --> 00:13:11,521
I don't care where an idea comes from,
and I don't appreciate you accusing me...

222
00:13:11,591 --> 00:13:12,615
It wasn't an accusation.

223
00:13:12,692 --> 00:13:16,493
- Then what would you call it?
- A respectful and sincere question.

224
00:13:18,498 --> 00:13:19,522
What's the answer?

225
00:13:22,568 --> 00:13:25,037
My objective opinion is...

226
00:13:26,673 --> 00:13:28,403
a minimally invasive
approach is best.

227
00:13:30,410 --> 00:13:31,410
Okay.

228
00:13:32,679 --> 00:13:35,547
I want it all mapped out with
a 3D reconstruction simulation

229
00:13:35,615 --> 00:13:37,743
before we go in there.
We'll operate in the morning.

230
00:13:45,391 --> 00:13:47,121
It's actually kind of soothing.

231
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:53,057
It reminds me of the dripping
faucet in our old apartment.

232
00:13:53,132 --> 00:13:55,158
- The sound helped me fall asleep.
- Hmm.

233
00:13:56,969 --> 00:13:58,267
I loved that building.

234
00:13:59,372 --> 00:14:00,931
It's where we had our first hug.

235
00:14:03,843 --> 00:14:05,539
Definitely not soothing.

236
00:14:11,217 --> 00:14:13,914
This might help.

237
00:14:14,787 --> 00:14:17,586
You brought earplugs
to a camping trip?

238
00:14:18,291 --> 00:14:19,291
Sometimes you snore.

239
00:14:20,927 --> 00:14:21,927
Thank you.

240
00:14:37,410 --> 00:14:38,605
Mm. Ooh!

241
00:14:47,153 --> 00:14:48,746
That's it, I give up.

242
00:14:51,391 --> 00:14:53,121
I have a repair kit.

243
00:14:53,192 --> 00:14:55,821
I don't want to fix things,
Shaun. I just want to go home.

244
00:15:01,634 --> 00:15:03,227
Don't want to go home.

245
00:15:04,070 --> 00:15:07,404
If you want to stay in a cold,
wet, leaky tent, go ahead.

246
00:15:07,473 --> 00:15:08,964
But I am sleeping in the car.

247
00:15:27,860 --> 00:15:31,160
Ah, 29:32.

248
00:15:31,230 --> 00:15:33,995
I used to do sub-25
on recovery days.

249
00:15:34,734 --> 00:15:37,101
